38. One can make good use of different leaves,<lb/>
especially aflame with various colors:<lb/>
yellow, green oak-leaves, the pale leaf of willow stems.<lb/>
One should not finish Tree-tops  <lb/>
as entirely round, as if they were trimmed or combed,<lb/>
but display branches growing densely on all sides<lb/>
of the trunks, most substantial down below,<lb/>
but letting them thin out above.<lb/>
</ab>

<ab><margin>left-middle</margin>Different leaves and colors of the Trees.</ab>
<ab><margin>left-middle</margin>Not making the Treetops round.</ab>
